<TEXT>The partial derivative formula_42 can be seen as another function defined on "U" and can again be partially differentiated. If all mixed second order partial derivatives are continuous at a point (or on a set), "f" is termed a C function at that point (or on that set); in this case, the partial derivatives can be exchanged by Clairaut's theorem:
</TEXT>
